<body class="ignore-math">
<h4 class="heading"><span class="type">Paragraph</span></h4>
<p>It looks like we broke our own rule in lines two and three in the above table of integration rules.  After all,</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
\int \dx{f} +\int \dx{g} = f+c_1+g+c_2
\end{equation*}
</div>
<p class="continuation">where  and  are arbitrary constants, and</p>
<div class="displaymath process-math" data-contains-math-knowls="">
\begin{equation*}
a\int\dx{y}=a(y+c)=ay+ac\text{.}
\end{equation*}
</div>
<span class="incontext"><a href="section-2.html#p-21" class="internal">in-context</a></span>
